ZEsarUX (ZX Spectrum Next / tbblue) - NextBASIC editor syntax highlighting
==========================================================================

What it does
    Colours the NextZXOS/NextBASIC full-screen editor, SpecNext-IDE style:

        statements  (PRINT, LET, GO TO, IF, THEN...)   blue
        functions   (RND, INT, CHR$, PEEK...)          magenta
        numbers                                        red
        strings                                        green
        REM comment text                               cyan
        line numbers, variables, operators             black (unchanged)

    Colouring is live: it follows the listing while you scroll, wraps
    correctly across continued lines, and updates as you type. Program
    output while a program RUNs is left uncoloured, as are the NextZXOS
    menus, the cursor and anything else that is not a listing line.

How it works
    The editor draws each character in its own 8x8 cell with attribute 38h
    (black ink on grey paper), so every glyph can be given its own ink
    colour without changing machine behaviour. Once per frame the patch
    reads the ULA screen (RAM 5), recognizes each cell by a CRC32
    fingerprint of its 8-byte bitmap (matching the editor font of the
    NextZXOS release bundled with ZEsarUX), parses rows that start with a
    BASIC line number (plus their wrapped continuations) and rewrites the
    attribute cells. Only cells whose attribute is the editor's own 38h
    (or a colour set by this patch) are ever touched; unrecognized glyphs
    and non-listing rows simply stay black.

Activation
    Inert unless the environment variable ZESARUX_NEXTBASIC_HIGHLIGHT=1
    is set. Requires the normal Spectrum core (the default).

    If a future NextZXOS release changes the editor font, highlighting
    degrades gracefully to no colouring (nothing else breaks); the
    fingerprint table in machines/tbblue.c is regenerated from a screen
    dump in that case.

How to apply (against https://github.com/chernandezba/zesarux master)
    cd zesarux
    git apply /path/to/zesarux-nextbasic-highlight.patch

    Independent of zesarux-nextbasic-hostdisk.patch: apply either one or
    both, in any order.

    Then build as usual, e.g.:
    cd src && ./configure && make

Verified
    Against ZEsarUX master 7d33f6b (13.1-SN, July 2026) with the bundled
    tbblue.mmc (NextZXOS 2.06H): coloured listings including wrapped
    string lines and REM lines, live recolouring while typing, uncoloured
    program output during RUN, untouched menus and cursor.

